\subsubsection*{Survival analysis}

The {\bf R} package {\tt eha} \citep{eha, ehar12} is used, and the
explanatory variables are almost the same as in the Poisson regression
analysis. The difference is that instead of mother's birth date, the
infant's birth date is used (no big difference), and a new variable, \emph{mother's age at child birth}, is introduced. It is centered around age 32. Other covariates, \emph{parity}, \emph{infant's birth date}, etc. are omitted, since they do not contribute much to the model. 

